          <div class="partner-tier tier-now">Right Now</div>
          <div class="partner-name">Too Good To Go</div>
          <div class="partner-why">You have already made organic content about this app twice. You have a quote ready: "this is not sponsored, I'm just personally invested in more people using it." That is your pitch to them in one sentence. Convert organic enthusiasm to a paid relationship.</div>
          <div class="partner-rate">Est. rate at 5K: $100 to $300 per integration</div>
        </div>
        <div class="partner-card">
          <div class="partner-tier tier-now">Right Now</div>
          <div class="partner-name">Beehiiv or Substack</div>
          <div class="partner-why">Newsletter platforms actively sponsor creators who talk about newsletters. You are building one. This is a natural fit and they run creator ambassador programs with free plans and rev-share. Apply now at any follower count.</div>
          <div class="partner-rate">Ambassador programs: usually product + commission</div>
        </div>
        <div class="partner-card">
          <div class="partner-tier tier-now">Right Now</div>
          <div class="partner-name">Teva</div>
          <div class="partner-why">You already posted an organic endorsement: "they are Mary Kate Olsen approved," "rappelled up a waterfall in these," "$50." That is a better ad than most brands write themselves. Email their influencer team with the video link. This is a warm outreach, not a cold pitch.</div>
          <div class="partner-rate">Est. rate at 5K: product + $150 to $400</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 32px;">Tier 2: Target at 10K to 30K</h3>

      <div class="partner-grid">
        <div class="partner-card">
          <div class="partner-tier tier-mid">10K to 30K</div>
          <div class="partner-name">NYC Co-Working Spaces</div>
          <div class="partner-why">You said you want to do a "co-working spots in NYC" video. That video, plus a partner tag from a co-working space, is a natural content-first deal. Industrious, Spaces, WeWork all have creator programs. Mullen Chelsea is already on your list.</div>
          <div class="partner-rate">Est. rate: free membership + $300 to $800</div>
        </div>
        <div class="partner-card">
          <div class="partner-tier tier-mid">10K to 30K</div>
          <div class="partner-name">Ness (HSA card) or Lively</div>
          <div class="partner-why">Your HSA gym hack video is the exact use case these fintech HSA companies market around. A "how I paid for Equinox with pre-tax dollars" integration is plug-and-play for them. Your audience skews exactly right: post-grad NYC, financially aware, earning real income.</div>
          <div class="partner-rate">Est. rate: $500 to $1,200 per video</div>
        </div>
        <div class="partner-card">
          <div class="partner-tier tier-mid">10K to 30K</div>
          <div class="partner-name">Blueground or June Homes</div>
          <div class="partner-why">You already name-dropped both of these as summer housing options. They run creator affiliate programs. At 10K with an apartment-focused audience they will pay for a dedicated segment. Frame it as "here's when managed housing actually makes sense" to keep it honest.</div>
          <div class="partner-rate">Est. rate: $400 to $1,000 + affiliate commission</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 32px;">Tier 3: At Scale (40K to 100K)</h3>

      <div class="partner-grid">
        <div class="partner-card">
          <div class="partner-tier tier-late">40K+</div>
          <div class="partner-name">NYC Restaurants + Hospitality</div>
          <div class="partner-why">Once your "ABC Eats" series has history and your food content is established, NYC restaurants will pay for your opinion. Not just a free meal, an actual fee. You have the cultural credibility to charge for placement in your ratings series because your reviews have teeth.</div>
          <div class="partner-rate">Est. rate: $800 to $2,500 per integration</div>
        </div>
        <div class="partner-card">
          <div class="partner-tier tier-late">40K+</div>
          <div class="partner-name">Airbnb / Travel</div>
          <div class="partner-why">Your El Salvador content shows you travel with a strong editorial voice. Airbnb and boutique travel brands (Elsewhere, Selina, Secret Escapes) sponsor creators at this tier when the content style matches. Your "accidentally found top 100 restaurant" format is their exact desired outcome.</div>
          <div class="partner-rate">Est. rate: $1,500 to $4,000 + trip coverage</div>
        </div>
        <div class="partner-card">
          <div class="partner-tier tier-late">40K+</div>
          <div class="partner-name">Fintech / FIRE adjacent (Credit Karma, Monarch Money)</div>
          <div class="partner-why">Your money hack content positions you well for fintech partnerships. Broker fee math, HSA optimization, library card ROI. Creators who make personal finance feel casual and human are extremely valuable to financial brands that need to not seem boring.</div>
          <div class="partner-rate">Est. rate: $1,200 to $3,500 per video</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="margin-top: 24px;">
        <div class="card-title"><span class="card-icon">📩</span> Outreach Template Formula</div>
        <p>Keep all cold outreach to under 5 sentences. Formula:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Sentence 1: What you already made about them (with the link).</li>
          <li>Sentence 2: Your audience profile in one specific data point (e.g., "primarily women 23 to 32, post-grad NYC, financially engaged").</li>
          <li>Sentence 3: What you are proposing specifically.</li>
          <li>Sentence 4: What it costs. Or "open to discussing."</li>
          <li>Sentence 5: A single question to prompt a reply.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

